A judge banned five girls – three of whom are 16 and two 15 – from travelling abroad after they showed an interest in going to Syria. 

He ordered their passports to be taken off them and for them to be made wards of the court.

Four of the girls, from Bethnal Green Academy, are associated with the four girls who have already joined IS to become ‘jihadi brides’. The fifth is schooled at home. 

Concerns for their welfare were raised by police after classmates Kadiza Sultana, 16, Shamima Begum, 15, and Amira Abase, 15, fled to Syria last month.

