 The trio followed in the footsteps of 15-year-old Sharmeena Begum, also from Bethnal Green Academy, who left for Syria in December.

Mr Justice Hayden made the move to bar travel following an application from Tower Hamlets social services. He was told social workers had raised concerns that the girls might flee to areas controlled by IS.

A number of adults involved in their care have also had their passports seized. There was evidence to suggest family members had not been ‘full and frank’ with social services, the judge said, and the girls were becoming ‘more radicalised’.

The judge said the identity of the five girls should not be revealed but the name of the school could be published because most staff and pupils would know who they were.

